      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That erratic, seemingly random nature is the most frustrating part, and it often points towards transient network instability or aggressive middle-box timeouts. Sometimes, even if the NAT Gateway metrics look okay, there can be brief periods of packet loss or routing hiccups that look like a sudden peer reset. Another possibility, especially if you have proxies or firewalls *in front* of the EC2 instances, is that they have very aggressive, short idle timeouts that are being triggered randomly by the fluctuating traffic patterns. It's like a sneaky, tiny brown-out of connectivity that the main metrics don't catch.",
      "source": "target",
